    ('BUS-K 360', 'VISUAL BASIC FOR APPLICATIONS (VBA) AND APPLICATION INTEGRATION', '12014', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 8:00 AM–9:15 AM', 'HH 4079', 'Amy Kinser', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Introduces students to VBA programming and Office application integration: Access, Excel, Word, PowerPoint, and Outlook. The purpose of this course is to develop the skills to enable students to create an integrated and fully automated business system or model and increase student''s ability to function as an efficient business person.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 507', 'INTRODUCTION TO SPREADSHEET MODELING', '9553', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 3:05 PM–4:35 PM', 'CG 2061', 'Joseph Baird', 4, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course will introduce students to the art and science of developing models that can be used to make better decisions. We will introduce students to optimization models (with EXCEL SOLVER and genetic algorithm SOLVER TABLE, and EVOLVER), simulation models, decision tree models and spreadsheet sensitivity analysis.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 507', 'INTRODUCTION TO SPREADSHEET MODELING', '14696', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 9:00 AM–12:00 PM', 'CG 3075', 'Fei Gao', 10, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course will introduce students to the art and science of developing models that can be used to make better decisions. We will introduce students to optimization models (with EXCEL SOLVER and genetic algorithm SOLVER TABLE, and EVOLVER), simulation models, decision tree models and spreadsheet sensitivity analysis.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 507', 'INTRODUCTION TO SPREADSHEET MODELING', '8425', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:15 AM–12:45 PM', 'CG 2061', 'Joseph Baird', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course will introduce students to the art and science of developing models that can be used to make better decisions. We will introduce students to optimization models (with EXCEL SOLVER and genetic algorithm SOLVER TABLE, and EVOLVER), simulation models, decision tree models and spreadsheet sensitivity analysis.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 513', 'PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS AND DATA MINING', '5878', 'Class Status', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 11:15 AM–12:45 PM', 'CG 2069', 'Jie Li', 10, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Large quantities of data are mined by organizations. However, managers struggle to obtain information that reliably facilitate decision making. Predictive analytics seeks to find patterns and classifications that look toward the future that enables managers to make strategic decisions.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 513', 'PREDICTIVE ANALYTICS AND DATA MINING', '5877', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:20 AM–10:50 AM', 'CG 2061', 'Jie Li', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Large quantities of data are mined by organizations. However, managers struggle to obtain information that reliably facilitate decision making. Predictive analytics seeks to find patterns and classifications that look toward the future that enables managers to make strategic decisions.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 529', 'CLOUD-BASED ANALYTICS', '7837', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:15 AM–12:45 PM', 'CG 1022', 'James Kinser', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'GODFREY GRAD&EXEC ED CTR', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The course focuses on querying databases, creating multi-user databases with navigation interfaces, and discuss setting the user experience. You will create dashboards using Excel features, Power BI tools (Power View, Power Pivot, Power Query, and 3D Map) of Excel along with the Power BI Desktop suite to visual your data.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 601', 'LINEAR OPTIMIZATION', '33885', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:30 AM–12:45 PM', 'HH 4146B', 'Kurt Bretthauer', 5, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course covers linear optimization. In particular, it focuses on theory, solution methods, and formulations for linear optimization problems. The goals are to give you the ability to read and understand research articles that use optimization techniques, and the ability to formulate models and develop solution methods for your research.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 602', 'INTEGER AND NONLINEAR OPTIMIZATION', '33884', 'Class Status', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:30 AM–12:45 PM', 'HH 4146B', 'Kurt Bretthauer', 5, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course covers integer and nonlinear optimization. It focuses on theory, solution methods, and formulations for integer and nonlinear optimization problems. It will give you the ability to read and understand research articles that use optimization techniques, and the ability to formulate models and develop solution methods for your research.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-K 635', 'SPECIAL TOPICS IN DECISION SCIENCES', '31805', 'Class Status', 'Tu Tuesday 1:00 PM–3:30 PM', 'HH 4146B', 'George Ball', 3, NULL, 'Lecture', '1.5', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Description will vary based on the topic offered.', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], NULL),
    ('BUS-L 100', 'PERSONAL LAW', '1187', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 12:45 PM–2:00 PM', 'WB WEB', 'Lynn Keller', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'WEB-BASED CLASS', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Examines effects of law on persons'' everyday lives. Areas studied may include such topics as family law; criminal offenses and traffic violations; personal injury and property damage claims; employee rights; landlord-tenant law; consumer rights; debt collection; selected real and personal property issues; wills and estates; selected contract law issues; and forms of business organization (partnership, proprietoryship, and corporation).', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
    ('BUS-L 201', 'LEGAL ENVIRONMENT OF BUSINESS', '1188', 'Closed', 'TuTh Tuesday, Thursday 9:35 AM–10:50 AM', 'HH 1006', 'Clovia Hamilton', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'Emphasis on nature of law through examining a few areas of general interest: for example, duty to avoid harming others (torts), duty to keep promises (contracts), and government regulation of business.', ARRAY['IUB GenEd S&H credit
